<h2 id="consumer" style="margin-top:48px">Understanding Ukrainian Consumer Behavior</h2>
<p>Before entering the Ukrainian market, understand how local consumers shop:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cash-on-delivery (COD) dominates:</strong> ~60% of online orders are paid upon delivery. This means your fulfillment partner must handle payment collection and reconciliation. MTP Group does this automatically through our &ldquo;Sheriff of Payments&rdquo; system.</li>
<li><strong>Nova Poshta is king:</strong> 10,000+ pickup locations. Most Ukrainians prefer picking up parcels at Nova Poshta offices rather than home delivery. Next-day delivery to Kyiv, 1-2 days nationwide.</li>
<li><strong>Price sensitivity:</strong> Average order value is $25-40. Consumers compare prices across platforms. Competitive pricing is essential.</li>
<li><strong>Mobile-first:</strong> 65%+ of online purchases happen on smartphones. Your product listings must be mobile-optimized.</li>
<li><strong>Seasonal peaks:</strong> Black Friday (November), New Year (December), March 8 (International Women&rsquo;s Day), and back-to-school (August-September) are the biggest shopping events. Prepare inventory 2-3 months in advance.</li>
<li><strong>Trust matters:</strong> Ukrainians trust established marketplaces (Rozetka especially) more than unknown brands. Starting on a marketplace gives you instant credibility.</li>
<li><strong>Anti-Russian sentiment:</strong> Since 2022, Ukrainian consumers actively avoid Russian brands and seek alternatives. This creates opportunities for European and American brands in categories like cosmetics, clothing, electronics, and software.</li>
</ul>

